= FactHarbor — Automated Fact-Checking for Newsrooms =

{{info}}
**Author:** Robert Schaub (Founder and Lead Developer, FactHarbor.ch) **Date:** 30 March 2026
{{/info}}

== What is FactHarbor? ==

FactHarbor is an **open-source tool for automated fact-checking**. It verifies any claim — topic-independent and multilingual — using publicly accessible sources, and delivers a transparent verdict with full source citations.

(% class="box warningmessage" %)
(((
**Open Source and Public-Interest Oriented**
No hidden algorithms, no proprietary scoring. Every step is traceable and inspectable.
)))

=== What it is NOT ===

FactHarbor does **not** replace editorial judgment, insider sources, or image/video verification (that's what InVID, TinEye etc. are for). It complements the existing toolbox by automating the time-consuming evidence research for **text-based claims**.

----

== How does it work? ==

Submit a claim → system researches automatically → transparent verdict with sources.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TD
    subgraph MAIN [" "]
        direction LR
        INPUT(["Claim\nor Article"])
        A["Extract verifiable\nstatements"]:::ai

        B["Search supporting\nand opposing evidence"]:::web

        Q["Filter quality\nand score sources"]:::ai
        C["Organize and\ncluster evidence"]:::ai

        subgraph DEBATE ["Structured AI Debate"]
            direction TB
            D["Advocate"]:::ai
            SC["Self-Consistency"]:::ai
            E["Challenger"]:::ai
            F["Reconciler"]:::ai
            V["Validator"]:::ai
            D --> SC & E
            SC & E --> F --> V
        end

        OUTPUT(["Verdict and\nStructured Report"])

        INPUT --> A --> B --> Q --> C --> DEBATE --> OUTPUT
    end

    subgraph LEGEND ["Legend"]
        direction LR
        L1["AI-powered"]:::ai ~~~ L2["Web and External Sources"]:::web
    end

    MAIN ~~~ LEGEND

    style INPUT fill:#2196F3,stroke:#1565C0,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style OUTPUT fill:#4CAF50,stroke:#2E7D32,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style DEBATE fill:#FCE4EC,stroke:#C62828,color:#B71C1C
    style MAIN fill:none,stroke:none
    style LEGEND fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#ccc,color:#666

    classDef ai fill:#E3F2FD,stroke:#1565C0,color:#0D47A1
    classDef web fill:#FFF3E0,stroke:#E65100,color:#BF360C
{{/mermaid}}

**Core principle:** Not a single AI call, but a **structured debate** — different AI models argue for and against a claim. Only evidence-backed objections count.

----

== What sets FactHarbor apart from existing tools? ==

|=Dimension|=OSINT Tools (InVID, Reverse Image Search etc.)|=FactHarbor
|**Scope**|Image and video verification|Text-based claims
|**Evidence research**|Manual — your own search|Automatic — iterative web research
|**Source quality**|Manual assessment|Automatic per-domain scoring
|**Contradiction detection**|Manual|Automatic — debate surfaces both sides
|**Time per claim**|2-4 hours (experienced journalist)|~15 minutes (target: < 5 min)
|**Traceability**|Your own notes|System documents every step + sources

